Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the React + Vite project.

## Changes Made:

### Modified Files:
- **src/App.jsx**
  - Added import statement for Analytics component from `@vercel/analytics/react` at the top of the file
  - Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the JSX return, just before the closing `</div>` of the main App component

### Package Information:
- The `@vercel/analytics` package (v2.0.1) was already installed in package.json
- No additional package installation was needed

## Implementation Details:

According to the official Vercel Analytics documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), for React applications using Vite, the setup requires:

1. Installing `@vercel/analytics` package ✓ (already installed)
2. Importing Analytics from `@vercel/analytics/react` ✓ (added to App.jsx line 2)
3. Adding the `<Analytics />` component to the main app component ✓ (added at line 886)

The Analytics component was placed at the end of the App component's JSX return statement, ensuring it will be rendered on every page and track all user interactions.

## Testing:

- Build verification: ✓ The project builds successfully with `npm run build`
- Build output: dist/index.html (0.81 kB) and dist/assets/index-CEpvqCXs.js (347.11 kB)
- No linter or test scripts were configured in package.json

## Next Steps:

To activate Web Analytics:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project Settings → Analytics)
3. Analytics data will start appearing after users visit the deployed site

The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation and integrates seamlessly with the existing React application structure.
